text: I loved it! It was not perfect but it was a fun movie (it was never meant to be Shakespeare, duh!). I don’t get why the VICIOUS & OVER-THE-TOP criticisms and pans. I went in without any expectations aside from knowing the premise of CHARLIE’S ANGELS. I thought Elizabeth Banks brought it further from its 1970’s roots and its 2000 & 2003 predecessors. Amazed at all the VITRIOL & HATE heaped on this movie.   Look, it never had any pretentious that it’s an Oscar-worthy movie but pure popcorn entertainment. And I’m a guy who is not intimidated by women kicking butt.   [NOTE*: There’s definitely a double-standard especially with “InCel Fanboys”. For example in AVENGERS:ENDGAMEthere’s long footage of Thor, Captain America, & Iron Man taking turns beating the crap out of Thanos—poses, posturing and all. Then with the brief moment when the female superheroes got together to help Spiderman women-haters were calling it “cringe-worthy, pushing a feminist agenda, social justice warrior bullcrap, etc.”...WTF?!! There really is something palpably and visibly wrong going on in our society that supposedly “strong, secure men feel immediately threatened with notions and images of powerful women. Why is that?! It’s the “21st Century” folks, Jeesh...are we STILL debating and arguing about the role, the place, & the potential of women in our society. IF we still are, then WE HAVE NOT PROGRESSED AS FAR AS WE THOUGHT WE HAVE.]
